translate ru strings:

    old "It had been weeks since Sarah first visited the library."
    new "It had been weeks since Sarah first visited the library."

    old "Ever since, her days had been possessed by a single focus. Studying."
    new "Ever since, her days had been possessed by a single focus. Studying."

    old "Razaphel, a constant, provided her a seemingly endless list of books to read."
    new "Razaphel, a constant, provided her a seemingly endless list of books to read."

    old "One subject more obscure than the next."
    new "One subject more obscure than the next."

    old "Ancient history texts on nations that Sarah had never even heard of."
    new "Ancient history texts on nations that Sarah had never even heard of."

    old "Primary Alchemical instruction manuals."
    new "Primary Alchemical instruction manuals."

    old "Even century old papers on the biology of obscure plant species."
    new "Even century old papers on the biology of obscure plant species."

    old "And Sarah read. She read everything he offered up to her, devouring the works."
    new "And Sarah read. She read everything he offered up to her, devouring the works."

    old "Perhaps there was a pattern to the chaos, but she had not yet managed to resolve it."
    new "Perhaps there was a pattern to the chaos, but she had not yet managed to resolve it."

    old "Sitting behind the desk, Sarah watched as the spirit manifested itself into the room again."
    new "Sitting behind the desk, Sarah watched as the spirit manifested itself into the room again."

    old "In its hand, a copy of a new book. One more for the pile."
    new "In its hand, a copy of a new book. One more for the pile."

    old "This is a book on non-native flora growth patterns."
    new "This is a book on non-native flora growth patterns."

    old "Sarah sighed, exhausted as she threw her current book down on the desk."
    new "Sarah sighed, exhausted as she threw her current book down on the desk."

    old "Are you ever going to explain why I have to read all this?"
    new "Are you ever going to explain why I have to read all this?"

    old "You know why. If you want to understand their order, you must broaden the context of your understanding."
    new "You know why. If you want to understand their order, you must broaden the context of your understanding."

    old "Sarah lifted up the tome that Razaphel had deposited."
    new "Sarah lifted up the tome that Razaphel had deposited."

    old "And a book on plants is going to do that?"
    new "And a book on plants is going to do that?"

    old "The spirit paused for a moment."
    new "The spirit paused for a moment."

    old "I understand that you are frustrated."
    new "I understand that you are frustrated."

    old "Will you trust me that in time, very soon, I can explain everything to you?"
    new "Will you trust me that in time, very soon, I can explain everything to you?"

    old "Sarah looked at the spirit. It's face-mask revealed nothing of its emotions. Its voice never wavered."
    new "Sarah looked at the spirit. It's face-mask revealed nothing of its emotions. Its voice never wavered."

    old "How could one ever deduce if such a creature lied or spoke the truth."
    new "How could one ever deduce if such a creature lied or spoke the truth."

    old "Then again, Sarah knew she had very few friends left that could help her with subjects of magic."
    new "Then again, Sarah knew she had very few friends left that could help her with subjects of magic."

    old "Say you trust the spirit"
    new "Say you trust the spirit"

    old "Yes...I trust you."
    new "Yes...I trust you."

    old "But even I have my limits, Razaphel."
    new "But even I have my limits, Razaphel."

    old "In time, you will have to bring me answers instead of books."
    new "In time, you will have to bring me answers instead of books."

    old "That time will come."
    new "That time will come."

    old "Say you don't trust the spirit"
    new "Say you don't trust the spirit"

    old "No, I don't trust you."
    new "No, I don't trust you."

    old "You've given me no reason to do so. All you've given me is an endless supply of books."
    new "You've given me no reason to do so. All you've given me is an endless supply of books."

    old "Books that leap from topic to topic like the list was drafted by a madman."
    new "Books that leap from topic to topic like the list was drafted by a madman."

    old "Who knows, maybe you are mad and I'm just wasting my time."
    new "Who knows, maybe you are mad and I'm just wasting my time."

    old "The spirit spun in the air."
    new "The spirit spun in the air."

    old "I promise that I will earn you trust, but only in due time, Sarah."
    new "I promise that I will earn you trust, but only in due time, Sarah."

    old "The answers will come. One day we shall speak truthfully."
    new "The answers will come. One day we shall speak truthfully."

    old "With that, the spirit vanished."
    new "With that, the spirit vanished."

    old "Staring at the book that remained, and the massive tome that had just been added to her list of work to do, Sarah sighed."
    new "Staring at the book that remained, and the massive tome that had just been added to her list of work to do, Sarah sighed."

    old "Falling back into her chair, she looked at the ceiling."
    new "Falling back into her chair, she looked at the ceiling."

    old "In only a moment, she realized that whatever work remained, would have to be done another day. She was done, her brain more than exhausted."
    new "In only a moment, she realized that whatever work remained, would have to be done another day. She was done, her brain more than exhausted."

    old "No sooner had Sarah thought the thought, than she heard the creaking of the floorboards."
    new "No sooner had Sarah thought the thought, than she heard the creaking of the floorboards."

    old "Samayra's animated voice seemed to lighten up the room."
    new "Samayra's animated voice seemed to lighten up the room."

    old "Sarah smiled at Samayra as she entered the room."
    new "Sarah smiled at Samayra as she entered the room."

    old "What is it Samayra?"
    new "What is it Samayra?"

    old "Samayra walked up towards the desk and planted her palms on the surface, leaning forward."
    new "Samayra walked up towards the desk and planted her palms on the surface, leaning forward."

    old "For a moment, she looked deadly serious. Gathering her words."
    new "For a moment, she looked deadly serious. Gathering her words."

    old "I'm bored."
    new "I'm bored."

    old "You have a whole magical house, and you're bored?"
    new "You have a whole magical house, and you're bored?"

    old "Samayra rolled her eyes."
    new "Samayra rolled her eyes."

    old "Only so often that I can go to the bathhouse."
    new "Only so often that I can go to the bathhouse."

    old "And unlike you, I can't spend all day reading."
    new "And unlike you, I can't spend all day reading."

    old "Sarah swiftly poked Samayra, causing her to leap back, startled."
    new "Sarah swiftly poked Samayra, causing her to leap back, startled."

    old "Maybe it would do you some good, filling up that head with something other than love stories."
    new "Maybe it would do you some good, filling up that head with something other than love stories."

    old "Samayra scowled at her, but Sarah struggled to ever take the girl's anger very seriously."
    new "Samayra scowled at her, but Sarah struggled to ever take the girl's anger very seriously."

    old "Well, I spend all my life in a palace, locked up. I don't want to be locked up here, reading more books!"
    new "Well, I spend all my life in a palace, locked up. I don't want to be locked up here, reading more books!"

    old "I'm going to go out."
    new "I'm going to go out."

    old "Sarah leapt up from her chair."
    new "Sarah leapt up from her chair."

    old "Samayra, you can't go out alone. Lethram is not...it's not a safe city."
    new "Samayra, you can't go out alone. Lethram is not...it's not a safe city."

    old "There are parts of this city that are really dangerous, and if you don't know what parts to avoid..."
    new "There are parts of this city that are really dangerous, and if you don't know what parts to avoid..."

    old "Well, I guess in that case I'll need a guide."
    new "Well, I guess in that case I'll need a guide."

    old "Samayra stuck out her tongue at Sarah."
    new "Samayra stuck out her tongue at Sarah."

    old "Still, are you going to let me walk out there all by myself?"
    new "Still, are you going to let me walk out there all by myself?"

    old "No. I'll come with you."
    new "No. I'll come with you."

    old "To be honest, I was kind of looking for a distraction anyway."
    new "To be honest, I was kind of looking for a distraction anyway."

    old "Samayra had a wide smile on her face."
    new "Samayra had a wide smile on her face."

    old "Great, then let's go!"
    new "Great, then let's go!"

    old "Samayra had already rushed for the door before Sarah was well and ready."
    new "Samayra had already rushed for the door before Sarah was well and ready."

    old "Rushing out behind her, Sarah tried to keep up with Samayra's energy."
    new "Rushing out behind her, Sarah tried to keep up with Samayra's energy."

    old "Sarah let her eyes drift across the study room."
    new "Sarah let her eyes drift across the study room."

    old "It was this house."
    new "It was this house."

    old "She needed a break."
    new "She needed a break."

    old "I have to get some fresh air."
    new "I have to get some fresh air."

    old "She spoke the words to nobody, and received as much as a reply."
    new "She spoke the words to nobody, and received as much as a reply."

    old "Sarah walked to the door and stepped outside, leaving the house and all her work behind her."
    new "Sarah walked to the door and stepped outside, leaving the house and all her work behind her."

    old "Stepping out of the house, Sarah was struck by the sudden wave of external stimuli."
    new "Stepping out of the house, Sarah was struck by the sudden wave of external stimuli."

    old "By now it was early in the afternoon and the city of Lethram had long buzzed to life."
    new "By now it was early in the afternoon and the city of Lethram had long buzzed to life."

    old "Inside the house, there was a distance, everything felt muted when watching the city through the windows."
    new "Inside the house, there was a distance, everything felt muted when watching the city through the windows."

    old "But outside, in the open, everything felt raw and real."
    new "But outside, in the open, everything felt raw and real."

    old "The noises. The rushing waves of people. The smells of a big city."
    new "The noises. The rushing waves of people. The smells of a big city."

    old "Sarah felt uneasy for a moment, so exposed."
    new "Sarah felt uneasy for a moment, so exposed."

    old "A part of her wanted to run back inside, but she also knew she could not live in that house forever."
    new "A part of her wanted to run back inside, but she also knew she could not live in that house forever."

    old "Sarah could see Samayra was standing out on the street."
    new "Sarah could see Samayra was standing out on the street."

    old "The girl seemed amazed."
    new "The girl seemed amazed."

    old "Sarah remembered herself when she had first come to Lethram. She had been no less impressed by the city."
    new "Sarah remembered herself when she had first come to Lethram. She had been no less impressed by the city."

    old "Samayra had lived even more isolated than Sarah had when growing up, so it was no surprise that it impressed her."
    new "Samayra had lived even more isolated than Sarah had when growing up, so it was no surprise that it impressed her."

    old "I...wow, it's-, I can't!"
    new "I...wow, it's-, I can't!"

    old "Samayra stumbled over her own words as she tried to formulate a thought."
    new "Samayra stumbled over her own words as she tried to formulate a thought."

    old "Let's go, I think there's a place somewhere nearby."
    new "Let's go, I think there's a place somewhere nearby."

    old "Sarah lead and Samayra dutifully followed, gazing in stunned amazement of all the sights."
    new "Sarah lead and Samayra dutifully followed, gazing in stunned amazement of all the sights."

    old "Sarah decided to force herself to start walking."
    new "Sarah decided to force herself to start walking."

    old "Motion. Keep moving. Make the body move before the mind has time to convince itself otherwise."
    new "Motion. Keep moving. Make the body move before the mind has time to convince itself otherwise."

    old "Walking through the streets of Lethram, Sarah followed the curving road."
    new "Walking through the streets of Lethram, Sarah followed the curving road."

    old "All around her, people were rushing up and down, dragging carts, carrying crates."
    new "All around her, people were rushing up and down, dragging carts, carrying crates."

    old "Lethram was a busy city, and it was especially so during the day."
    new "Lethram was a busy city, and it was especially so during the day."

    old "So near to the market district, this was where most of the trade that came in through the harbor district was offloaded."
    new "So near to the market district, this was where most of the trade that came in through the harbor district was offloaded."

    old "The sea trade had made Lethram obscenely wealthy and had allowed it to maintain its independence as a city in a world dominated by larger nations."
    new "The sea trade had made Lethram obscenely wealthy and had allowed it to maintain its independence as a city in a world dominated by larger nations."

    old "Walking here, it made her reflect on how little she had known when she first left Rosanna."
    new "Walking here, it made her reflect on how little she had known when she first left Rosanna."

    old "Her homeland had been prosperous enough when she left, but it was nothing compared to this place."
    new "Her homeland had been prosperous enough when she left, but it was nothing compared to this place."

    old "Walking through these streets, she couldn't help but realize that this was a place where things seemed to happen."
    new "Walking through these streets, she couldn't help but realize that this was a place where things seemed to happen."

    old "A place of importance. A place that decided how the world moved."
    new "A place of importance. A place that decided how the world moved."

    old "That energy had never been in the air back home. Her home was a place of tradition and routine."
    new "That energy had never been in the air back home. Her home was a place of tradition and routine."

    old "There were times she found herself missing the security of that routine. Then there were times where Sarah loved the dynamism of this city."
    new "There were times she found herself missing the security of that routine. Then there were times where Sarah loved the dynamism of this city."

    old "As had been often of late, Sarah found her heart torn."
    new "As had been often of late, Sarah found her heart torn."

    old "Off to the side, Sarah could see a small crowd of people, gathered near a storefront, haggling over prices."
    new "Off to the side, Sarah could see a small crowd of people, gathered near a storefront, haggling over prices."

    old "Would she have been happier, she wondered, if she'd never taken a step on this path to begin with?"
    new "Would she have been happier, she wondered, if she'd never taken a step on this path to begin with?"

    old "Perhaps if she had just resigned herself to living a simpler life."
    new "Perhaps if she had just resigned herself to living a simpler life."

    old "But Sarah also knew it was too late for that. Too late for regrets."
    new "But Sarah also knew it was too late for that. Too late for regrets."

    old "Sarah saw the sign for a cafe."
    new "Sarah saw the sign for a cafe."

    old "She pointed it out to Samayra."
    new "She pointed it out to Samayra."

    old "Here, let's go to this one."
    new "Here, let's go to this one."

    old "Samayra nodded, following Sarah's lead."
    new "Samayra nodded, following Sarah's lead."

    old "She decided to go inside."
    new "She decided to go inside."

    old "Inside of the cafe, there was a calm atmosphere."
    new "Inside of the cafe, there was a calm atmosphere."

    old "A few patrons were seated by their own tables, occupied in their own conversations"
    new "A few patrons were seated by their own tables, occupied in their own conversations"

    old "Sarah sat down at one of the tables."
    new "Sarah sat down at one of the tables."

    old "Samayra sat down opposite of her."
    new "Samayra sat down opposite of her."

    old "Sarah smiled as she watched Samayra's wide eyes sliding across the room."
    new "Sarah smiled as she watched Samayra's wide eyes sliding across the room."

    old "Around them, waiters were rushing back and forth from the bar, taking and delivering orderse."
    new "Around them, waiters were rushing back and forth from the bar, taking and delivering orderse."

    old "It's just like the palace back home in Bagrad, except...the servants have servants?"
    new "It's just like the palace back home in Bagrad, except...the servants have servants?"

    old "This city is a little more equal than where you or I came from."
    new "This city is a little more equal than where you or I came from."

    old "People work, but even those that work make enough money to visit places like this."
    new "People work, but even those that work make enough money to visit places like this."

    old "Samayra nodded as she listened to Sarah explain."
    new "Samayra nodded as she listened to Sarah explain."

    old "So...none of these people are slaves?"
    new "So...none of these people are slaves?"

    old "Slavery is strictly forbidden in Lethram."
    new "Slavery is strictly forbidden in Lethram."

    old "Sarah could see Samayra process that fact."
    new "Sarah could see Samayra process that fact."

    old "Huh, my father had always said that slaves were a natural part of the world. How empires were build."
    new "Huh, my father had always said that slaves were a natural part of the world. How empires were build."

    old "But this city is pretty big, and it doesn't have slaves at all..."
    new "But this city is pretty big, and it doesn't have slaves at all..."

    old "If anything, it's likely Lethram has been wealthier than Bagrad for a good many centuries."
    new "If anything, it's likely Lethram has been wealthier than Bagrad for a good many centuries."

    old "Sarah saw Samayra's face suddenly turn sad."
    new "Sarah saw Samayra's face suddenly turn sad."

    old "I...never thought about it like that."
    new "I...never thought about it like that."

    old "Bagrad. The palace. Up until recently they were the only places I've ever known."
    new "Bagrad. The palace. Up until recently they were the only places I've ever known."

    old "Sarah saw the girl go quiet for a moment, then she looked up."
    new "Sarah saw the girl go quiet for a moment, then she looked up."

    old "Do you think I was a bad person for living in that palace?"
    new "Do you think I was a bad person for living in that palace?"

    old "For living with so much while others had so little?"
    new "For living with so much while others had so little?"

    old "Sarah reached over and took Samayra's hand."
    new "Sarah reached over and took Samayra's hand."

    old "I think that if you're even questioning these things, you're probably a lot better than most."
    new "I think that if you're even questioning these things, you're probably a lot better than most."

    old "And I think given where you were raised, you never had much of a chance to push back."
    new "And I think given where you were raised, you never had much of a chance to push back."

    old "Who knows, maybe if the world had played out differently, you might have inherited the throne and changed all of that."
    new "Who knows, maybe if the world had played out differently, you might have inherited the throne and changed all of that."

    old "Samayra nodded, but still seemed uncertain."
    new "Samayra nodded, but still seemed uncertain."

    old "Maybe...I don't know."
    new "Maybe...I don't know."

    old "You think you would have kept slavery?"
    new "You think you would have kept slavery?"

    old "Not that, but I think...I just never had to think about any of that."
    new "Not that, but I think...I just never had to think about any of that."

    old "I spend my life in the library. The gardens. I just had to do what my father told me."
    new "I spend my life in the library. The gardens. I just had to do what my father told me."

    old "Now...I'm here, and I see all of this...it's a lot."
    new "Now...I'm here, and I see all of this...it's a lot."

    old "I understand. I had a lot of the same feelings that you have when I first came here all those years ago."
    new "I understand. I had a lot of the same feelings that you have when I first came here all those years ago."

    old "All I had ever known was my homeland, the castle I had been raised in."
    new "All I had ever known was my homeland, the castle I had been raised in."

    old "When that was all gone...I felt lost too for a long time."
    new "When that was all gone...I felt lost too for a long time."

    old "It was magic that gave me a way back to getting some degree of control over my life."
    new "It was magic that gave me a way back to getting some degree of control over my life."

    old "Samayra smiled and nodded."
    new "Samayra smiled and nodded."

    old "Maybe that's what I need. Some way to get some control back."
    new "Maybe that's what I need. Some way to get some control back."

    old "Sure, but you're in no rush. You're safe in the house, in this city, with my protection."
    new "Sure, but you're in no rush. You're safe in the house, in this city, with my protection."

    old "You've been through a lot. The best thing for you now is to try and just recover."
    new "You've been through a lot. The best thing for you now is to try and just recover."

    old "Samayra eagerly nodded."
    new "Samayra eagerly nodded."

    old "I think some food might help with that."
    new "I think some food might help with that."

    old "Sarah laughed and raised her hand, calling over one of the waiters."
    new "Sarah laughed and raised her hand, calling over one of the waiters."

    old "Each gave their order and not long after the food was delivered. Money formed no problem, Sarah kept finding piles of it stashed away in the house."
    new "Each gave their order and not long after the food was delivered. Money formed no problem, Sarah kept finding piles of it stashed away in the house."

    old "Huh...fish..."
    new "Huh...fish..."

    old "Is that a problem?"
    new "Is that a problem?"

    old "No, we just didn't get a lot of that in Bagrad."
    new "No, we just didn't get a lot of that in Bagrad."

    old "We weren't very close to an ocean, and the merchants prefered to bring foods that could survive a trip through the desert."
    new "We weren't very close to an ocean, and the merchants prefered to bring foods that could survive a trip through the desert."

    old "Yeah, if you don't like fish, this city can be a problem."
    new "Yeah, if you don't like fish, this city can be a problem."

    old "Well I love fish."
    new "Well I love fish."

    old "With a growing hunger, each of them began to dig into their meal."
    new "With a growing hunger, each of them began to dig into their meal."

    old "As they ate their share, each swapped stories of their life from before they met."
    new "As they ate their share, each swapped stories of their life from before they met."

    old "It continued to surprise Sarah just how much she had in common with a girl who had been born on the other side of the world."
    new "It continued to surprise Sarah just how much she had in common with a girl who had been born on the other side of the world."

    old "The isolation of the castle. The weight of nobility. All were things that few people could share, but this girl understood intuitively."
    new "The isolation of the castle. The weight of nobility. All were things that few people could share, but this girl understood intuitively."

    old "Hey there ladies."
    new "Hey there ladies."

    old "All of a sudden, Sarah heard a familiar voice calling out to the both of them."
    new "All of a sudden, Sarah heard a familiar voice calling out to the both of them."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, she saw a man stand up next to the table."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, she saw a man stand up next to the table."

    old "Enjoying yourselves, I hope."
    new "Enjoying yourselves, I hope."

    old "Samayra looked at Alaric and smiled."
    new "Samayra looked at Alaric and smiled."

    old "Very much so, the food here is great!"
    new "Very much so, the food here is great!"

    old "Well I'm glad to hear that."
    new "Well I'm glad to hear that."

    old "Alaric reached out with one hand, and Samayra reacted, grabbing and shaking his."
    new "Alaric reached out with one hand, and Samayra reacted, grabbing and shaking his."

    old "Sarah lunged forward and pulled Samayra's hand back."
    new "Sarah lunged forward and pulled Samayra's hand back."

    old "Don't shake his hand."
    new "Don't shake his hand."

    old "Samayra seemed shocked and confused."
    new "Samayra seemed shocked and confused."

    old "Why not? Who is he?"
    new "Why not? Who is he?"

    old "Alaric continued to smile."
    new "Alaric continued to smile."

    old "Me? Ooh me and Sarah here are good friends, aren't we, Sarah?"
    new "Me? Ooh me and Sarah here are good friends, aren't we, Sarah?"

    old "I'm sure you have somewhere else to be. Maybe some old lady dropped her wallet nearby?"
    new "I'm sure you have somewhere else to be. Maybe some old lady dropped her wallet nearby?"

    old "Always funny running into you Sarah."
    new "Always funny running into you Sarah."

    old "And who knew you had such a lovely friend?"
    new "And who knew you had such a lovely friend?"

    old "But no, I actually don't have anywhere I need to be right now."
    new "But no, I actually don't have anywhere I need to be right now."

    old "Sarah stood up from the table."
    new "Sarah stood up from the table."

    old "Samayra, stay here."
    new "Samayra, stay here."

    old "Sarah grabbed Alaric by his shirt and began to drag him outside of the cafe."
    new "Sarah grabbed Alaric by his shirt and began to drag him outside of the cafe."

    old "Outside, the sun was already setting and the streets had grown significantly quieter."
    new "Outside, the sun was already setting and the streets had grown significantly quieter."

    old "Sarah continued to drag Alaric, off to the side of the cafe, away from anyone else."
    new "Sarah continued to drag Alaric, off to the side of the cafe, away from anyone else."

    old "Finally, far enough from prying eyes, Sarah released Alaric and turned to face him."
    new "Finally, far enough from prying eyes, Sarah released Alaric and turned to face him."

    old "You have a lot of fucking nerve coming over to me like that."
    new "You have a lot of fucking nerve coming over to me like that."

    old "As always, his face was painted with that casual and arrogant smile of his."
    new "As always, his face was painted with that casual and arrogant smile of his."

    old "I just thought it was funny running into you, and I saw your little girlfriend over there, quite a stunner, so I just thought-"
    new "I just thought it was funny running into you, and I saw your little girlfriend over there, quite a stunner, so I just thought-"

    old "Well don't."
    new "Well don't."

    old "Don't think, don't talk, don't do shit to cause trouble, do you understand?"
    new "Don't think, don't talk, don't do shit to cause trouble, do you understand?"

    old "You know or what!"
    new "You know or what!"

    old "Sarah felt the heat of magical fire rising from around her hands. She could turn him to ash as easily as the snap of her finger."
    new "Sarah felt the heat of magical fire rising from around her hands. She could turn him to ash as easily as the snap of her finger."

    old "Aah, yes, you're going to set me on fire, I remember."
    new "Aah, yes, you're going to set me on fire, I remember."

    old "He didn't seem all the impressed."
    new "He didn't seem all the impressed."

    old "But you see, there's a little problem that you've forgotten."
    new "But you see, there's a little problem that you've forgotten."

    old "You see, there are actually laws in Lethram."
    new "You see, there are actually laws in Lethram."

    old "Even for mages."
    new "Even for mages."

    old "So while you might have been in your right to kill me back at your house, cause I'll admit I was up to no good, out here..."
    new "So while you might have been in your right to kill me back at your house, cause I'll admit I was up to no good, out here..."

    old "Well everyone has seen I didn't do nothin but talk to a few pretty girls."
    new "Well everyone has seen I didn't do nothin but talk to a few pretty girls."

    old "And that hardly deserves the death penalty."
